The Seattle Seahawks are signing everybody to extensions. I wonder how much I'd have to chip in to get listed as "The Official Cheddar and Bacon Burger with Everything of the Seattle Seahawks."

Police in Mt. Morris, New York, apprehended three burglary suspects Sunday by following a trail of macaroni salad they left behind while making their getaway.

The Livingston County Sheriff's Office reports thieves broke in and stole a cash register from Build-A-Burger Restaurant, along with the establishment's entire surveillance system and a large bowl of macaroni salad.

Deputies were hot on the criminals' trail, literally, as they attempted to escape via the nearby Greenway Trail.

"Found along the trail were cash register parts, surveillance system parts, rubber gloves, loose change and a steady trail of macaroni salad," the sheriff's office said. "It was later discovered that the suspects stole a large bowl of macaroni salad, which they took turns eating, along their escape route."

Important note: We do not have macaroni salad at Gene's.

Drive safely.
